'''Thapelo Maseko''' (born 11 November 2003) is a South African professional [[Association football|soccer]] player who plays as a [[forward (association football)|forward]] for [[Mamelodi Sundowns F.C.|Mamelodi Sundowns]] and the [[South Africa national soccer team|South Africa national team]].

== Club career ==

Maseko is a youth product of [[SuperSport United F.C.]], where he started his professional career. He impressed during the [[2022–23 South African Premier Division|2022–23 season]], as he helped SuperSport to a third-place finish in the [[South African Premier Division|South African top league]].<ref name="sowetanlive"/> This reportedly earned him offers from the likes of [[Belgian Pro League|Belgian]] club [[K.V.C. Westerlo|KVC Westerlo]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://farpost.co.za/2023/07/18/sundowns-complete-the-signing-of-thapelo-maseko/ | title=Sundowns complete the signing of Thapelo Maseko | date=18 July 2023 }}</ref>

=== Mamelodi Sundowns ===
In June 2023, he signed for the [[Mamelodi Sundowns F.C.|Mamelodi Sundowns]], the record 13 time-winners of the [[South African Premier Division|Premier League]].<ref name="sowetanlive">{{cite web | url=https://www.sowetanlive.co.za/sport/soccer/2023-07-18-rising-star-thapelo-maseko-joins-sundowns/ | title=Rising star Thapelo Maseko joins Sundowns }}</ref> He played a fundamental role in the team that won the first [[African Football League]] in [[2023 African Football League|2023]], most notably scoring the only goal of the two semi-final legs against [[Al Ahly SC|Al Ahly]].<ref>{{Cite web |date=2023-10-29 |title=Thapelo Maseko the goal hero for Mamelodi Sundowns as Tshwane giants humble Percy Tau's Al Ahly |url=https://www.goal.com/en-za/lists/thapelo-maseko-the-goal-hero-for-mamelodi-sundowns-as-tshwane-giants-humble-percy-tau-s-al-ahly/blt5df3df0f0b39523e |access-date=2024-01-07 |website=Goal |language=en-ZA}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.africatopsports.com/2023/10/29/laf-demi-finale-aller-les-mamelodi-sundowns-battent-lal-ahly/ | title=LAF / Demi-finale aller : Les Mamelodi Sundowns battent l'Al Ahly | date=29 October 2023 }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web |last=Baleka |first=Mihlali |date=Oct 29, 2023 |title=Thapelo Maseko scores only goal of the game as Sundowns beat Al Ahly in first leg of AFL semi-final |url=https://www.iol.co.za/sport/soccer/africa/thapelo-maseko-scores-only-goal-of-the-game-as-sundowns-beat-al-ahly-in-first-leg-of-afl-semi-final-18c38381-ee26-4537-91a3-0e660a3e5dc3 |website=IOL}}</ref> He was the best player and top goal scorer of the competition.<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.africatopsports.com/2023/11/13/ligue-africaine-de-football-decouvrez-tous-les-prix-decernes/ | title=Ligue Africaine de Football : Découvrez tous les prix décernés | date=13 November 2023 }}</ref>

==== AEL Limassol ====
He was loaned to [[Cypriot First Division]] side [[AEL Limassol]] for the rest of the 2025/26 season in the January transfer.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Mbuyisa |first=Spelz |date=2026-01-11 |title=Vodacom Soccer {{!}} News {{!}} Thapelo Maseko tipped for a move to Cyprus from Mamelodi Sundowns |url=https://vodacomsoccer.com/news/thapelo-maseko-tipped-for-a-move-to-cyprus-from-mamelodi-sundowns-3 |access-date=2026-01-12 |website=Vodacom Soccer |language=en}}</ref>

== International career ==

Maseko is an international for [[South Africa national football team|South Africa]], having played the [[2022 COSAFA Cup]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.timeslive.co.za/sport/soccer/2022-07-14-mkhalele-pleads-with-psl-teams-to-give-his-bafana-youngsters-a-chance/ | title=Mkhalele pleads with PSL teams to give his Bafana youngsters a chance }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.news24.com/citypress/sport/mkhalele-takes-over-bafana-and-turns-to-fresh-talent-for-cosafa-cup-20220701 | title=Mkhalele takes over Bafana and turns to fresh talent for Cosafa Cup }}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.timeslive.co.za/sport/soccer/2022-06-28-ethan-brooks-to-lead-bafana-bafana-as-squad-assembles-for-cosafa-cup/ | title=Ethan Brooks to lead Bafana Bafana as squad assembles for Cosafa Cup }}</ref>

In January 2024, he was selected with South Africa for the [[2023 Africa Cup of Nations|2023 AFCON]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.citizen.co.za/sedibeng-ster/news/2024/01/05/maseko-will-represent-vaal-at-afcon/ | title=Maseko will represent Vaal at AFCON | date=5 January 2024 }}</ref>

